<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> General </F>
<H3> <TI>   ROK Says Suspension of `Team Spirit' `Conditional' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0303091594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0813 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0303091594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, March 3 (XINHUA) -- South Korea said today 
that it considers the suspension of "Team Spirit '94" joint 
military exercise with the United States conditional. 
  The South Korean Defense Ministry said in a statement that 
one condition is that the inspection of nuclear sites in the 
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) by U.N. Inspectors 
is "completed with success." 
  Another condition is that the DPRK and South Korea exchange 
special envoys to discuss "concretely" the nuclear issue, said 
the statement. 
  According to an agreement reached on February 25 in New York 
between the United States and DPRK, the United States would 
suspend "Team Spirit '94" joint military exercise with South 
Korea. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

