<F P=100> Northeast Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhu Rongji Visits Fukuoka, Addresses Banquet </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0303011894 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1625 
GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW0303011894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Zhang Huanli (1728 3562 0448)] </F>
  [Text] Fukuoka, 1 Mar (XINHUA) -- Japan's Fukuoka 
Prefectural government, the Fukuoka Prefectural Sino-Japanese 
Friendship Association, and the Kyushu Yamaguchi Economic 
Association held a grand banquet at the New Otani Hotel in 
Hakata this evening to warmly welcome Chinese Vice Premier Zhu 
Rongji and his party on their arrival in Fukuoka. 
  Fukuoka Prefecture Governor Hachiji Okuda gave a welcome 
speech at the banquet. He said: Fukuoka is an important port 
in the 2,000-year history of exchanges between Japan and China. 
It has established friendly relations with China's Jiangsu 
Province. In addition, four cities in the prefecture have 
established friendship ties with Chinese cities. The Fukuoka 
people are ready to take further steps to help develop 
friendship and cooperation between Japan and China. 
  In his speech, Zhu Rongji praised Fukuoka Prefecture for its 
relentless efforts to develop Sino-Japanese friendship not only 
in the past but also at the present. Zhu Rongji said: 
Sino-Japanese economic and trade relations have developed 
rapidly in recent years. However, Fukuoka still has great 
potential for developing economic relations with China. I hope 
the two sides will work hard to continue to expand cooperation 
between Fukuoka and China. 
  Before concluding their visit to Osaka, Zhu Rongji and his 
party also visited Okayama Prefecture, where they visited the 
Seto Ohashi Bridge. Zhu Rongji praised the ocean bridge for its 
magnificent construction and attractive layout. He also 
inquired about the economic benefits obtained from the bridge's 
construction. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

