<H3> <TI>   Zhu Rongji Visits Kitakyushu City </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0303010394 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1641 
GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW0303010394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Zhang Huanli (1728 3562 0448)] </F>
  [Excerpts] Kitakyushu, 2 Mar (XINHUA) -- Koichi Sueyoshi, 
mayor of Japan's Kitakyushu city, and persons in charge of local 
economic circles today hosted a dinner at the Kitakyushu Royal 
Hotel to welcome Zhu Rongji and his party. [passage omitted] 
  At the dinner, Zhu Rongji expressed the hope that 
cooperation 
between Kitakyushu city and China would continue. 
  This afternoon, Zhu Rongji and his party visited Yasugawa 
Electric Machinery Company, Japan's largest manufacturing plant 
for industrial-use robots. 
  In the morning, Zhu Rongji visited Japan's wellknown Toto 
Electric Company's First Sanitary Porcelain Plant in Kokura, and 
heard a briefing by company President Yoshine Koga on its 
cooperation with China. Zhu Rongji expressed the hope that Toto 
Electric Company would further its cooperation with and transfer 
its technology to China. Zhu Rongji said: With an urban 
population of 300 million, China has a very large market and the 
prospects for cooperation between the two sides are very bright. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

