<H3> <TI>   Departs Maldives for Iran </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0303111994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1055 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0303111994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Male, March 3 (XINHUA) -- Chinese vice premier and 
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen left here today for Iran en route 
from Karachi, Pakistan, after his two-day official goodwill 
visit to the Maldives. 
  Qian was seen off by Maldivian Foreign Minister Fathulla 
Jameel and other Maldivian Government officials and Chinese 
Ambassador to the Maldives Zhang Chengli at the Male 
International Airport. 
  During the visit, Qian exchanged views with Jameel on 
bilateral relations and regional and international issues of 
common interest. The two sides also signed an aviation agreement 
and another agreement on economic and technical cooperation. 
  The Maldives is the fourth country of Qian's current 
five-nation tour. Qian visited Pakistan, Bangladesh and Sri 
Lanka before coming to the Maldives. 

