<H3> <TI>   Qiao Shi Meets Palau Delegation in Beijing </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0203135594 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1237 
GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW0203135594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 2 (XINHUA) -- Chairman Qiao Shi of 
the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC) 
had a warm and friendly conversation on furthering China-Belau 
[Palau] ties here today with a congressional delegation from 
this island country in West Pacific. 
  Qiao expressed the hope that Belau, a trustee of the United 
States, will win full independence at an early date in 
accordance with its people's desire. 
  Describing the delegation's visit as a good beginning for 
promoting Sino-Belau relations, Qiao hoped for more exchanges 
between the two sides after Belau's independence. 
  Qiao also reaffirmed China's consistent position that 
countries, big or small, strong or weak, should be equals and 
all countries must respect each other and have the right to go 
their own ways in the light of different conditions. 
  The visitors, led by Yutaka Gibbons, who is the chief 
Aibedul, arrived here yesterday. 
  Gibbons thanked the hosts for their hospitality and 
expressed 
the hope that Belau and China will have more contacts. 
  Present at the meeting was NPC Vice-Chairman Li Peiyao. 
After the meeting, Li hosted a dinner in honor of the visitors. 

</TEXT>

