<H3> <TI>   Chinese Officials Renew Terms of Advisers on Hong Kong </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0203203494 Beijing XINHUA in English 1628 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0203203494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shenzhen, March 2 (XINHUA) -- The first group of 43 
Hong Kong people from all walks of life, who have just finished 
a two-year term as Hong Kong affairs advisers, will continue 
their service with an invitation renewal ceremony held here 
today. 
  Presenting the certificates for the renewal to the advisers 
including Fok Ying-tung were Lu Ping, director of the Hong Kong 
and Macao Affairs Office under the State Council, and Zhou Nan, 
director of XINHUA news agency Hong Kong branch. 
  At the ceremony, Lu Ping spoke highly of the valuable 
opinions and suggestions the advisers made over the past two 
years for Hong Kong's transition and the transfer of government 
in 1997. 
  "This shows your sense of responsibility for realizing the 
'one country, two systems' concept, achieving the smooth 
transition, and maintaining prosperity and stability in Hong 
Kong," Lu said. 
  Analyzing the current situation in Hong Kong, he said that a 
series of unilateral actions the Hong Kong British authorities 
took recently demonstrated their determination to continue the 
policy of confrontation with China in three years odds [as 
received] before 1997. 
  This will help all kindhearted people have a clearer 
knowledge about the British side, cast away the illusion for 
"cooperation", a lip service by the British side, and strengthen 
"our resolve to guarantee Hong Kong's smooth transition together 
with our Hong Kong compatriots," Lu said. 

</TEXT>

