<F P=100> TAIWAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Economic Minister Views Ties With Mainland </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0303062394 Taipei Voice of Free China in English 0200 GMT 
2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW0303062394 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei Voice of Free China </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "News" program] </F>
  [Text] Economic Minister P. K. Chiang stated on Tuesday [2 
March], when answering questions from lawmakers in the 
Legislative Yuan, that to ensure economic development, raise 
industrial competitiveness, and lower production costs, the 
Economic Ministry is clear about the state of relations between 
the two sides of the Taiwan Strait and will keep the ties more 
or less at the present level. However, Chiang said that serious 
discussions must be carried out on point-to-point direct 
navigation links and even in an across-the-board opening of 
navigation and aviation links in the future. However, Chiang 
stressed that since the opening of navigation links between the 
two sides is covered in the medium- term-part of the national 
unification guideline, any research done on this issue and the 
results coming from them should be forwarded to the Mainland 
Affairs Council for reference. He said that the result will be 
help to policy makers when the time comes for further opening up 
of ties between the two sides. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

