<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hu Jintao Calls For Strengthening of CPC </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0203205294 Beijing XINHUA in English 1457 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0203205294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 2 (XINHUA) -- Enhancing the build-up 
of the Communist Party of China (CPC) is a key to China's 
further development and to building socialism with Chinese 
characteristics, a party leader said here today. 
  Hu Jintao, member of the Standing Committee of the Political 
Bureau of the Central Committee of the Chinese Communist Party 
(CPC), made the remarks at a forum to mark the fifth anniversary 
of the birth of the magazine, "THE STUDY OF PARTY CONSTRUCTION." 
  The magazine is run by the Organization Department of the 
CPC 
Central Committee. 
  Hu praised the magazine's progress in the study of the 
party's construction and publicity work over the past five years 
and urged the magazine to make new contributions in its field. 
  He said that in the new period, there were many experiences 
and problems in the construction of the party which call for 
study with a long-term view and with an overview of the whole 
international and domestic situation. 
  He stressed the role of the party's leadership in the 
improvement of the party's construction. 
  Other Chinese leaders -- Jiang Zemin, Li Peng and Qiao Shi 
-- 
wrote messages to the magazine. 

</TEXT>

