<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jiangsu Reports Record Freshwater Fish Output </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0203095994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0738 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0203095994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Nanjing, March 2 (XINHUA) -- Output of freshwater 
fish in east China's Jiangsu Province set the highest record in 
history last year, enabling the province to become the country's 
second with freshwater-fish production exceeding one million 
tons. 
  As a famous time-honored land of rice and fish, Jiangsu has 
rich aquatic resources with 1.7 million ha [hectares]. In total 
acreage of fresh water. 
  During the past decade, the provincial government has 
boosted 
the development of freshwater fish-farming as part of the 
efforts to readjust agricultural structure and increase farmers' 
income. 
  To meet the demand of markets, importance has been given to 
raising of rare and special species, and artificial cultivation 
of crabs, pearls, eels and soft-shelled turtles, which have 
become new pillars of local freshwater farming. 
  Based on the burgeoning of aquatic breeding, new economic 
entities combining cultivation, processing and export of aquatic 
products have come into being and effectively promoted the 
expansion of export-oriented fish-farming. 
  By now, annual exports of aquatic products from Jiangsu have 
reached 20,000 tons with total profits worth 100 million U.S. 
dollars. 
  Jiangsu has also stressed spread of technology in order to 
gain high quality, high efficiency and high output in aquatic 
breeding. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-1958 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi042_o_94005" </HT>


