<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shanghai Mayor Huang Ju Vows To Boost Foreign Trade </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0203041994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0202 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0203041994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, March 2 (XINHUA) -- This, China's largest 
economic center has vowed to boost foreign trade this year. 
  According to Huang Ju, mayor of the city, Shanghai plans to 
export 8.5 billion U.S. dollars-worth of goods this year, an 
increase of 15.4 percent over last year and exceeding the growth 
of its gross domestic product. 
  Last year saw the city export 7.34 billion U.S. 
dollars-worth, keeping the same pace with the expansion of its 
GDP. 
  "However, Shanghai's leading position in economic 
development 
has required it to further develop its foreign trade," the mayor 
noted. 
  Huang called on foreign trade departments to strive to 
export 
at least 8.5 billion U.S. dollars-worth of goods this year and 
goods valued at 10 billion U.S. dollars next year. 
  To accomplish the objective, the municipal government has 
decided to adjust its industrial structure and organize 
enterprise groups while adopting an investment policy to 
encourage foreign trade departments. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

