<H3> <TI>   Shanghai Mayor Meets Former Secretary of State Eagleburger </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0203035394 Shanghai People's Radio Network in Mandarin 
2300 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW0203035394 </F>
<F P=104>  Shanghai People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Morning News" program] </F>
  [Text] Mayor Huang Ju met yesterday evening with former 
U.S. Secretary of State Lawrence Eagleburger and his party at 
the Jinjiang Hotel. The guests and their host had a warm and 
friendly conversation. 
  During the meeting, Huang Ju briefed the guests on 
Shanghai's 
economic achievements. While speaking about utilizing foreign 
funds, Huang Ju pointed out that currently the United States was 
the largest foreign investor in Shanghai. He warmly welcomed 
U.S. entrepreneurs accompanying Eagleburger to invest in 
Shanghai and participate in cooperative projects. 
  Eagleburger highly praised the drastic changes in Shanghai's 
appearance in recent years. He reiterated the importance of 
U.S.- PRC cooperation for world peace, and expressed his 
willingness to continue to work to promote cooperation between 
the two countries. 
  Yesterday Eagleburger visited the Pudong New Area, the 
Shanghai Stock Exchange, and the city's foreign exchange 
regulation center. 

</TEXT>

