<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shanghai Aircraft Plant Supplies Spare Parts to U.S. Firm </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0203014594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0112 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0203014594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, March 2 (XINHUA) -- Out of the many 
global counterparts of McDonnell Douglas [MD], the aircraft 
manufacturing giant in the United States, the Shanghai Aircraft 
Factory has now developed into its number one overseas spare 
parts supplier. 
  At present, it has sold 261 total sets of spare parts to MD, 
including both simple products like main landing-gear doors and 
advanced ones like electronic cabin doors and tailplanes which 
set more strict demands on technology and skills. 
  The Shanghai Aircraft Factory has played an important role 
in 
Sino-U.S. high-tech cooperations during recent years. 
  Apart from active competition on the world's spare parts 
markets, it has also introduced advanced technology and 
management experience from McDonnell Douglas to jointly 
manufacture MD-82 and MD-83 aircrafts. 

</TEXT>

