<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhejiang Forms Largest Fluorination Industrial Base </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0303092994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0730 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0303092994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hangzhou, March 3 (XINHUA) -- East China's Zhejiang, 
one of China's few provinces which abound in fluorite ore, has 
over the past decade developed the country's top fluorination 
industrial base. 
  Official sources said that by the end of this century, an 
estimated output value of more than three billion yuan will be 
realized by the fluorination industry of the province. 
  At present, the fluorination industrial sector is capable of 
producing about ten types of products, including basic 
fluorination materials, elementary fluoride and fluo-medicine, 
according to official sources. 
  In the past decade, the province has invested a total of 
some 
470 million yuan to introduce advanced technology and equipment 
such as instruments for the production of anhydrous hydrofluoric 
acid and methane-chloride, in support of the technological 
development of its fluorination industry. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

