<H3> <TI>   Shenzhen To Build Auto Manufacturing Center </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0303125494 Beijing XINHUA in English 0641 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0303125494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shenzhen, March 3 (XINHUA) -- Shenzhen City, one of 
China's special economic zones, is to build an auto 
manufacturing center, according to local government sources. 
  The center will aim to put new life into the city's auto 
industry, and thus promote related industries. 
  In the government plan, by the year 2000 auto manufacturing 
will become one of the city's pillar industries, with an output 
of ten billion yuan, accounting for ten percent of Shenzhen's 
total industrial output that year. 
  In its preliminary efforts, the city government will invest 
150 million yuan (about 17.2 million U.S. dollars) in the 
construction of the center. 

</TEXT>

