<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shenzhen Taxi Drivers Reportedly Stage Strike </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0303102794 Hong Kong AFP in English 0856 GMT 3 March 93 </F>
<F P=103> HK0303102794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hong Kong, March 3 (AFP)--Taxi drivers in China's 
special economic zone of Shenzhen went ahead with a strike 
Thursday to protest against the authorities issuing new taxi 
licences, residents said. The majority of the taxis operating 
in the zone at the border with Hong Kong halted services in what 
was believed to be the first major strike by taxi drivers in 
China, residents, contacted by telephone, said. 
  The taxi drivers, though disorganised with no apparent 
leaders, were protesting against the issuing of 2,000 licences 
to operators of new taxis in the Shenzhen. There were about 
6,500 taxis in the zone run by more than 80 taxi companies, with 
over 10,000 drivers. 
  There was a "visible" increase in the number of armed police 
officers patrolling the streets, travellers returning from the 
zone said. 

</TEXT>

