<F P=103> HK0103083294 </F>
<F P=104>  Haikou Hainan People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Du Qinglin, chairman of the provincial people's 
congress standing committee and provincial party committee 
deputy secretary, met Mr. Hwang In-chong, president of the ROK 
Development Research Academy, at the China Hainan Reform and 
Development Research Academy yesterday afternoon. The two sides 
exchanged views on economic cooperation between Hainan and the 
ROK and some other issues. 
  When giving an account of Hainan's achievements over the 
past 
six years since the Hainan Special Economic Region was 
established, Chairman Du Qinglin noted: There are now more than 
5,000 foreign- funded enterprises in Hainan, 13 of which are 
ROK-funded enterprises, ranking 14th in numerical order among 
all the foreign investors in Hainan. Many ROK conglomerates 
have expressed an interest in investing in Hainan. We welcome 
all of them to come and invest here. 
  Mr. Hwang In-chong said: Though relatively backward with 
regards to its level of development, Hainan is more advanced in 
urban management in comparison to the ROK. The 100,000 
qualified personnel Hainan has invited from other Chinese 
provinces and regions have now become your biggest asset. I am 
convinced that Hainan's numerous preferential policies are bound 
to attract more investment from the ROK and other foreign 
countries. 

