<F P=100> Southeast Asia &amp; Pacific </F>
<H3> <TI>   Qian Qichen Meets With Maldivian President </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0303093394 Beijing XINHUA in English 0909 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0303093394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Male, March 3 (XINHUA) -- Visiting Chinese 
Vice-premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen called on 
Maldivian President Maumoon Abdul Gayoom here today. 
  During their meeting, Qian conveyed an invitation of Chinese 
President Jiang Zemin to Gayoom to visit China at a convenient 
time. 
  He said Gayoom's visit to China in 1984 has promoted the 
development of cooperative relations between the two countries. 
  Qian noted that "China and the Maldives have shared common 
views on many international issues and the two countries have 
been active in developing their bilateral relations". 
  He believed that with joint efforts, cooperations will 
further develop in various fields of the two countries. 
  Gayoom said, Qian's current visit "will be another milestone 
in the development of the friendly relations between the two 
countries". 
  He also spoke highly of the fast economic development in 
China in the past decade. 
  Gayoom asked Qian to convey his invitation to Chinese 
President Jiang Zemin to visit the Maldives and expressed the 
hope that he will pay another visit to China in the near future. 

</TEXT>

