<F P=100> HONG KONG &amp; MACAO </F>
<F P=101> Hong Kong </F>
<H3> <TI>   Lu Ping Praises Hong Kong People's Abilities, Contributions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0303062094 Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE in Chinese 1115 
GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0303062094 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Wang Min (3769 2549)] </F>
  [Text] Shenzhen, 3 Mar (ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE)--Despite the 
difficulties caused by the obstacles resulting from the British 
side's uncooperative attitude and confrontation in the course of 
China resuming sovereignty over Hong Kong, we have a powerful 
motherland backing us and enjoy the concerted efforts of the 
Hong Kong compatriots. There are no difficulties or dangers 
which cannot be overcome, and there are no obstacles which 
cannot be removed. Lu Ping, director of the State Council's 
Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office, made these remarks today at 
a ceremony to present certificates for the continuation of 
service of the first group of Hong Kong affairs advisers. 
  Lu Ping thanked the Hong Kong affairs advisers for raising a 
large number of valuable opinions and suggestions through 
various forms and channels on a number of issues relating to 
Hong Kong's power transfer and steady transition since their 
appointment. Lu Ping said: On one hand, the appointment of the 
Hong Kong affairs advisers manifests their sense of 
responsibility for materializing "one country, two systems" and 
Hong Kong's steady transition in 1997 as well as for preserving 
Hong Kong's stability and prosperity; on the other, it also 
gives expression to the Chinese Government's determination to 
ensure the implementation of the policy of "Hong Kong people 
administering Hong Kong" and to practice a high degree of 
autonomy in Hong Kong. 
  Lu Ping continued: Several days ago, the British Hong Kong 
Legislative Council ratified parts of the draft legislation 
formulated according to Chris Patten's "constitutional reform 
package," and the British Government published a White Paper on 
the substance of the Sino-British talks on the constitutional 
structure. These unilateral moves -- which undermine cooperation 
-- suggest that the British side will willfully continue to 
pursue a policy of confrontation during the transitional period 
of a little more than three years. This behavior will only 
drive all kindhearted people to heighten their vigilance and 
abandon any illusions about the British side's empty promise of 
so-called "cooperation." 
  Lu Ping also cited Deng Xiaoping's remarks from 10 years 
ago: 
"We should believe that the Hong Kong Chinese can properly 
administer Hong Kong. The disbelief that Chinese people can 
properly administer Hong Kong was inherited from the old 
colonialist school of thought." "The prosperity of Hong Kong 
was created by the Hong Kong people, who are primarily Chinese." 
"The Hong Kong people are able to administer Hong Kong 
properly, and we must have this confidence." 
  In conclusion, Lu Ping said: In the near future, we will 
invite a third group of Hong Kong affairs advisers, who will 
come from all social levels and fields in Hong Kong. The ranks 
of the Hong Kong affairs advisers are growing, and they will 
play a more important role in bringing about the recovery of 
Hong Kong's sovereignty. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

