<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Song Jian Calls For Development of High-Tech Industry </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0103204194 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0837 
GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW0103204194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Xu Jiling (1776 2623 3781)] </F>
  [Text] Nanjing, 18 Feb (XINHUA) -- While inspecting Jiangsu 
recently, Song Jian, State Councillor and the minister in charge 
of the State Science and Technology Commission, called on those 
who work in new and high technology development zones not only 
to attract foreign funds and import technologies but also to 
attach high importance to promoting the commercialization, 
industrialization, and internationalization of the domestic 
scientific and technological results and to accelerating the 
pace of the development of China's new and high technology 
industry. 
  Song Jian inspected new and high technology development 
zones 
in Suzhou, Wuxi, and Changzhou and new and high technology 
enterprises in the Torch Plan belt of Suzhou, Wuxi, and 
Changzhou from 11 to 17 February. He said that one of the 
conspicuous characteristics that comes from comparing a new and 
high technology development zone to an economic development zone 
is that the former places even more emphasis on the 
transformation of domestic scientific and technological results. 
He also noted the need to formulate more preferential policies 
and to provide better conditions for large and medium-sized 
enterprises, scientific research institutes, and colleges and 
universities to set up branches in the zone to carry out the 
large-scale production of new and high technology products. 
  Song Jian also spoke of the need to strive to upgrade 
industry's scientific and technological levels, to greatly raise 
productivity, and to help transform traditional industry into 
new and high technology industry. He said that because China's 
new and high technology industry is now in the beginning stage, 
it is essential for the development zone to provide a 
development base for this budding industry and to become an 
experimental and demonstration zone for establishing a new 
system. He called for promoting cooperation among large and 
medium-sized enterprises and scientific research institutes, and 
to give support to private scientific and technological 
enterprises and to big enterprise groups with an annual output 
value between 1 billion and 10 billion yuan, so that they will 
hold a big market share of the domestic market and compete on 
the international market. Song Jian held that the absorption of 
foreign capital and the import of foreign technologies are an 
important way to accelerate the development of China's new and 
high technology industry. He pointed out, however, the need to 
assimilate, master, and upgrade imported technologies so that 
they will help build China's superiority in technology. 
  To upgrade industry, Song Jian called for devoting efforts 
to 
train a large number of high-level and 
internationalization-minded scientists and technicians. He also 
called for the attracting of a number of doctorate and master's 
degree holders and foreign-trained scholars with strong 
technical backgrounds, commercial skills, and excellent foreign 
language proficiency to work at leading organs and management 
departments in the development zone. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

