<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Carries Economic News Briefs for 2 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0203014694 Beijing XINHUA in English 0020 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0203014694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 2 (XINHUA) -- Today's economic news 
briefs: 
Tianjin Company To Be Listed in HK [Hong Kong] [subhead] 
  A Tianjin-based chemical firm, the Tianjin Bohai Chemical 
(Group) Co.,Ltd., which is the biggest salt chemical production 
center in China, will soon be listed in Hong Kong. 
<H5>  Sheet Glass Furnace in Operation </H5>
  China's first electronic sheet glass production furnace has 
gone into operation in Qinhuangdao, a port city in north China's 
Hebei Province. 
  It can produce electronic glass sheet from 0.5 mm to 3 mm 
thick for the electronics, energy, and medical and health 
industries. 
  The total investment in the project is 110 million yuan, and 
it will have an annual glass production of 2.41 million sq m. 
<H5>  Steel Output </H5>
  The total steel production output of the Shougang (Capital 
Iron and Steel) Corporation in 1993 hit over seven million tons, 
with 3.98 million tons, about 60 percent of the total, produced 
by continuous casting. 
  The company's steel output in 1992 was 5.7 million tons, and 
continuous-cast steel totalled 2.76 million tons in the same 
year. 

</TEXT>

