<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Homes Exhibition Opens in Beijing </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0103040094 Beijing XINHUA in English 0316 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0103040094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 1 (XINHUA) -- The first Chinese 
exhibition of houses built for sale on the open market opened 
here Monday [28 February]. 
  With the country's 100-plus real estate companies taking 
part, the exhibition has been mounted in Beijing's 
newly-completed building material mansion. 
  The exhibition is sponsored by the Construction Commission 
of 
the Beijing municipal government and jointly hosted by the 
Beijing real estate development market and the Dayin Real Estate 
Exhibition Center. 
  Being displayed are the achievements and recent development 
of real estate all over the country. Deals on houses of various 
grades built for sale on the open market are taking place at the 
event. 
  Personnel from the municipal housing management departments, 
banks and legal departments are on hand at the exhibition to 
handle on the spot such matters as transfer of ownership for 
house-buyers. 
  The Beijing municipal government has also provided 
well-designed apartments -- on sites totalling two million 
square meters in area -- for sale at the exhibition so that 
ordinary salary-earners can enter the house market as well. 

</TEXT>

