<DATE1>  4 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> United States &amp; Canada </F>
<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Reports U.S. Reinstates Super 301 Trade Law </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0303205194 Beijing XINHUA in English 2032 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0303205194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Washington, March 3 (XINHUA) -- U.S. President Bill 
Clinton signed an executive order here today reinstating the 
defunct Super 301 trade law, America's ultimate weapon in 
forcing trade concessions from foreign countries. 
  Speaking at a White House ceremony this afternoon, U.S. 
Trade 
Representative Mickey Kantor called the Super 301 a "strong 
market opening tool." 

</TEXT>

